# APPENDIX C — AI Cake Studio Backend Implementation Context

**Last updated:** 8 July 2026
**Status:** Implementation in progress

---

## 1. What We're Building

A **backend service for AI cake image generation** that:
- Takes user inputs (prompt, style, occasion, flavor, zodiac)
- Generates cake design images via AI provider
- Stores images permanently on S3
- Persists all metadata in a dedicated PostgreSQL schema
- Makes designs searchable and reusable for recommendations
- Tracks generation history per customer
- Is provider-agnostic (switch AI models via config, not code)

---

## 2. Architecture Decisions Made

| Decision | Choice | Rationale |
|----------|--------|-----------|
| AI Provider (current) | Replicate FLUX.1-pro | Best cost-to-quality ratio, ₹2–3 per generation, zero initial investment |
| AI Provider (future) | OpenAI DALL-E 3 | Can switch via env var when budget allows |
| Provider architecture | Interface + Adapter pattern | Change provider = change env var, zero code changes |
| Image storage | AWS S3 (existing bucket: `pranajiva-innovations`) | Already configured, no new infra |
| S3 prefix | `ai-studio/cake-designs/` | Clean separation, generic top-level, task-specific subfolder |
| S3 file path | `ai-studio/cake-designs/{generation_id}/design-{index}-{short_uuid}.png` | No customer PII in URLs, CDN-friendly |
| Database | Separate PostgreSQL schema: `ai_studio` | Clean separation from Medusa core tables |
| Core table | `ai_studio.cake_designs` — one row per generated image | Each image is independently searchable, saveable, orderable |
| Grouping table | `ai_studio.generations` — one row per generation request | Links multiple designs, tracks cost/status/timing |
| Search (MVP) | Attribute-based: style + occasion + flavor + tags | Simple, effective, no extra infra |
| Search (future) | pgvector embeddings for visual similarity | Phase 3 enhancement |
| Tags | Auto-derived from prompt + attributes | GIN-indexed for fast filtering |
| Backend brand logic | None — completely brand-agnostic | Frontend decides who sees this feature |
| Recommendations | Public designs shown to other users as inspiration | `is_public`, `is_featured`, engagement counters |

